  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 29:28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 29:28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Full of days — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Fully satisfied with the days which God had given him, having had the happiness of seeing his beloved son Solomon settled in his throne. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Riches and honour — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He had enough of this world, and of the riches and honour of it; and he knew when he had enough. He was satisfied, and very willing to go to a better place.",
        "children": []
      },
