  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he died in a good old age,.... Being seventy years of age: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "full of days, riches, and honour; had as much of either of them as he could wish for; and having enough, he sought after, and was taken to the possession of, eternal life, durable riches, and honours, and glory, that fade not away: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Solomon his son reigned in his stead; in full power and authority. ",
        "children": [
